      <para id="id1169837738087">[LO 2.1]</para>
      <list id="id4843525" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic">
        <item>Different communities have different needs and do not always succeed in meeting all their needs. As communities become more successful in meeting their needs, their standard of living improves.</item>
      </list>
      <para id="id1169843248363">People who have a low income mainly strive to meet their need for survival, while communities who have higher incomes are able to afford luxuries and fulfil their desires in addition to meeting their need for survival.</para>
      <list id="id4297938" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic">
        <item>In the following two illustrations two different communities in South Africa are depicted. Study them thoroughly and do a comparative study with the help of the table.</item>
